# Commit Message Template

## Format
```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
```

## Types
- **feat**: New feature
- **fix**: Bug fix
- **docs**: Documentation only
- **style**: Code style (formatting, missing semi-colons, etc.)
- **refactor**: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
- **test**: Adding missing tests
- **chore**: Changes to build process or auxiliary tools

## Examples

### Initial implementation
```
feat(ci): implement KinD-based load testing pipeline

- Add multi-node KinD cluster provisioning with ingress support
- Deploy echo services (foo/bar) with host-based routing
- Implement HTTP load test with percentile metrics (p90, p95, p99)
- Automate PR comments with load test results
- Add health checks with retry logic

Closes #1
```

### Bug fix
```
fix(load-test): correct success rate calculation

Previously counted only HTTP 200 responses; now validates
response body contains expected text ("foo" or "bar").

Fixes #42
```

### Documentation
```
docs(readme): add troubleshooting section

Addresses common issues with localhost DNS resolution
and Docker socket permissions.
```
